summary: In the French Open tennis tournament, defending champion Iga Swiatek emerged victorious for the fourth time, surpassing Serena Williams' legacy. Despite the pressure of being undefeated, Swiatek remained composed and dominated throughout the tournament. The rivalry between Swiatek and Gauff is anticipated to continue as Gauff strives to close the gap. Swiatek's impressive performance showcased her dominance on clay courts, earning her the title of "baking hot" at the French Open. Odds and predictions for the 2024 French Open women's final suggest that Swiatek remains the favorite to retain her crown.

summary: In a series of alarming incidents, three separate shark attacks have occurred along the Florida Panhandle and California coast in recent days. name: Wheel of Fortune
summary: In a flurry of emotional farewells and heartwarming tributes, the final episode of "Wheel of Fortune" with Pat Sajak as host airs on Friday after an impressive 41-year run. Sajak's departure marks the end of an era for the beloved game show, which has become a cultural staple. The host's influential introduction 43 years ago left an unforgettable mark on the show's legacy. As Sajak bids adieu, his former co-host Vanna White expressed her sentiments in an emotional tribute. The show's impact is also reflected in the significant prize winnings that have transformed contestants' lives. Sajak's final message in his last episode is bound to be filled with reminiscences and gratitude for his time on the show. As Sajak departs, questions arise about Ryan Seacrest's ability to fill his shoes as the new host, while other sources provide insights into Sajak's career and the enduring popularity of "Wheel of Fortune."

name: William Anders
summary: William Anders, a former NASA astronaut and US Air Force major general, passed away at the age of 90 while piloting a plane that crashed in the San Juan Islands. Anders was most well-known for his iconic "Earthrise" photograph taken in 1968 during the Apollo 8 mission, which provided a full view of Earth from space. His passing has been mourned by NASA Administrator Bill Nelson, who remembered Anders' contributions to space exploration and his dedication to sharing the wonders of space with the public.

name: Casper Ruud
summary: Alexander Zverev defeated Casper Ruud in the French Open semifinals, setting up a final match against Carlos Alcaraz. Ruud expressed disappointment over a stomach problem that hindered his performance. Tennis experts predicted Zverev's victory in the semifinals. Ruud also participated in an off-court quiz as part of his Roland Garros experience. While Zverev reached the French Open final, his case in Germany was resolved on the same day. Ruud acknowledged Zverev's determination and looked forward to a rematch against Novak Djokovic in another Grand Slam tournament. Live streaming options were available for the Ruud vs. Zverev match. Zverev's victory was attributed to Ruud's physical ailment and his own powerful performance. Ruud reflected on his stomach issues and expressed satisfaction with his overall French Open result.
